<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?> <FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="2"> <Content><Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE IN:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. RAY AND MAHI'S HOME - late afternoon - 2021</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A twenty something year old MA'AT (brown skinned, thick hair, looks like the princess of some far away kingdom) lies face-down on a bed, wearing jeans and a plaid shirt in a room that seems to belong to a little girl. She's holding a Teddy bear and crying quiet tears.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">JAGAN (military demeanor, but still bright-eyed for someone who's seen so much) walks in sporting a military regulation haircut and a clean-shaven face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Baby. It's time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at cleans up her face a little from the tears she's trying to hide, and places the aged bear on a dresser. Next to it is an inhaler that Jagan spots.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Whose is that?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's from when I was younger.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">She takes a deep breath and gathers herself before stepping out of the room with him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The two come down a hallway and meet face to face with RAY, (Ma'at's father, dark skinned and grounded with kind eyes) who's now well into his fifties.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You guys got everything packed?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan nods.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And we stocked your kitchen with as much as it can hold, so... you guys won't have to venture out for a while.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">May-May, you need to marry this boy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto, and very pleased with herself)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I did, Daddy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh, that's right. You did, didn't you? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(turning to Jagan)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well he'd better take good care of you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">He always does.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There's plenty of room for you at the house, Ray. And it's far from the cities and the rioters--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I told you two already. This is it for me. Everything I need is right here in this house.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">People are getting desperate.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm not leaving.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at takes her father's hand. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Did Mama put a spell on you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray nods.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Before you were born. Now go see her. She's been waiting for you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">These are somber times. Ma'at walks past the men in her life and leaves them standing there to continue their conversation.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dragging her fingertips along the walls as if she wants to take in these moments with all of her senses, Ma'at heads down the hallway leading to a sun room. Plant life is the decoration here as light pours in. In a chair, we can make out the silhouette of a queen. We see where Ma'at gets her poise. MAHI (mother to Ma'at, a child of the sun, bright with twisted flowing locks) sits with her feet up beside her on cushioned wicker furniture and a paintbrush in her hand. The canvas in front of her looks like it's a nearly finished piece of work.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at walks in cautiously. The closer she gets, the more she sees that her mother's normally bright lips are noticeably blue as well as her fingertips. She takes frequent breaks between her brushstrokes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Without looking up or breaking stride, Mahi speaks to her daughter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What gives life?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at's eyes are filled with love and pain at the sight of her dying mother. Still standing in the doorway, she manages to answer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Life is the giver of life. Everything in the universe conspires to make more life...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Mahi takes a break to gaze on her daughter and smile.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">By simply existing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. RAY AND MAHI'S HOME - hallway</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray and Jagan are as they were. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Things are gonna get worse before they get better. It's a good drive to where you're headed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yeah, I know. But at least we're not traveling alone. There's a guy from my old RECON unit that's meeting us on the road with his family.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray ponders this a moment, concerned.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do you trust him?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">With my life.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray gives Jagan all the weight of the world with his next question.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But do you trust him with </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">her</Text>
<Text Style=""> life? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Street - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan's face still pondering Ray's question. From the outside we can see that the couple is inside of a black family SUV, barreling down the road. Ma'at, riding shotgun is looking through the window into the fast approaching evening sky, no doubt still processing that she's just seen her mother for the last time. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Another truck is in front of them, a dusty pickup holding Jagan's friend MCCONNOR (redheaded Marine, rough around the edges) his wife, CARMEN and their young son. Various shots from the POV of both men show them casing their surroundings, and checking on their loved ones in their prospective vehicles.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan rubs a hand on Ma'at to comfort her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You holdin' up ok?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at turns to give a pained smile. She turns back to the window as...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A white luxury sedan blows the horn as it rockets past them, blasting music from the SPICE GIRLS. The driver holds his middle finger out of the window as he passes. The tag reads, GET BNT. It's annoying but almost funny to Jagan and McConnor. Carmen holds tight to her son and McConnor rubs behind the boy's head and gives him a kiss atop it. Ma'at in the other vehicle grabs tightly to Jagan's arm to calm her anger and settles in for the ride ahead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">After more driving, Jagan and McConnor notice headlights in the distance.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From the outside we can see them getting close to a group of vehicles that are stopped. A couple of unmarked police vans, a truck and uniformed men. It's a makeshift barricade.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JagAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Climb in the back. Put that blanket over your head.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at observes the sight ahead and moves over the seats to settle in the back where all of their belongings are piled up. McConnor looks over at his wife and child. In the small cab of his pick up truck, his family doesn't have the luxury of being able to hide.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A uniformed "CHECKPOINT OFFICER" approaches the same white car that passed everyone on the road earlier. The driver, a prick seems to be in a hurry. Let's call him, MITCH. In the passenger seat next to him is ASHLEE (40's, fit, a Hollywood trophy wife type). She's wearing shades and filing her nails.  </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Mitch</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hey! This obstruction you guys have here, is llligal and I don't have time for this shit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where are you headed?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MITCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. Lemme stop you right there.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(Hand officer a business card)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And that E.S.Q. behind my name means I'll have your career ended when I file a complaint.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The officer looks at him, smiles. Doesn't budge.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MiTCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. You think I'm joking. What's your badge number?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This is a checkpoint. As you may know, the plague has already claimed half of all women.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MiTCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(pointing to Ashlee)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well, as you can plainly see she's not sick.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ashlee</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(still filing her nails, not looking up)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm not sick.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Good. That's real good. You look healthy... </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ashlee looks up for the first time, pleased at the officer's comment. Winks at Mitch who rolls his eyes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So to insure you stay that way, we'll be taking you to a safe house in which we'll be able to provide you with the proper care.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MiTCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hang on. No. We're not going to any safe house, we're taking a boat, that is waiting for us and getting off this goddamn coast. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Officer looks at Mitch as tensions begin to rise.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I wasn't talking to you. There isn't room at the houses for more, "swinging dicks".</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A few of the uniformed guys around inch closer. Mitch is now visibly nervous and fumbles with a pen and paper.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MITCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What, um, what was your badge number and, and name, officer?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Checkpoint OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do I look like I'm wearing a fucking badge?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MITCH</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh, okay. Okay. Alright I'll give you what you want.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Mitch fumbles through his pockets and finds several hundred dollar bills. Ashlee looks over nervously as he thumbs through them before handing them over to the armed man.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The checkpoint officer looks at them for a moment, then back at the other men. He stands straight up, grabs the money and turns around as if to count it. Mitch and Ashlee settle a bit. The officer turns back around and the bills are aflame in his hand and burning quickly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The other men laugh.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You think this is still worth something? Mitch, this is a whole new world... and people like you, ain't gonna last.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The officer releases the burning money, which falls to the ground in slow motion as Mitch follows it with his eyes. Immediately the officer pulls out his handgun and POW! He shoots Mitch in the head. Blood splatters on Ashlee as she screams. The other men violently yank her out of the vehicle. The men take turns pulling on her in a way that lets us know that this is just the beginning of how she will be handled later.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CHECKPOINT OFFICER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(walking away from the scene)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Get her in the van so we can get to these next two.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and McConnor from each of their vehicles have watched this entire scene play out. Ma'at, watching from under the veil of an old blanket is horrified as Ashlee screams while being forced into a police style van. Through everything, we begin to hear the sound of a heartbeat.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Intercutting from between the two families, Jagan and McConnor are giving their wives identical instructions.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Stay down...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Stay quiet...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">...and no matter what you hear...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">...don't get out. If something happens...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">...drive away, and never look back.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Both ladies nod as the uniformed men get closer to the vehicles. Jagan and McConnor both ready the weapons they keep stashed beside them. McConnor tightens the grip on his rifle, Jagan slides his handgun from between the seats. The heartbeat gets louder and faster and both men are approached by the armed aggressors. Jagan makes eye contact with McConnor who gives him a nod and with that, they both yank open their doors to...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Smash CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Blackness</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The heartbeat continues in the blackness as we hear different sounds of the coming scene building as well. Dusty air, heavy breathing, restlessness.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE IN:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Trader shop - AFTERNOON - 2027</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We fade in on the chest of DUSTY (Early 40's, narrow build of unknown descent) and realize that it's his panicked heartbeat we've been feeling. We move to his shifty eyes as he shuffles about the inside a dimly lit shop. The fleeting sunlight his only source of clarification. He tries to part his overgrown, matted brown hair as he searches the store's crates frantically for something. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">He finds it, grabs it and nervously makes his way over to the front of the shop. We finally see what he found so necessary to obtain as he drops what looks to be a bag of dog food on a dusty wooden counter. The man behind the counter TRADER, (50's stout and bald) looks at Dusty's selection and takes a glance at him. He takes a break from carving something that's not very amazing out of a small block of wood in his hands, and slides it to the side. There's a sawed-off shotgun on the counter next to him, and you know he's used it. Probably today.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">trader</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's a lotta food there. What you got to trade?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dusty places a wristwatch on the counter. It's not new, but nothing in this world is anymore. But it's metal and it's heavy. Trader gives the watch a sublte, gleamy eyed once over.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TRADER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nobody uses these anymore. Can't get fucking batteries, and time don't mean shit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Dusty</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It... It doesn't use batteries. Works off motion.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Trader shakes the watch a little, puts it to his ear to listen and is a little more pleased. Slides the watch in his pocket.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TRADER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And what else you got?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dusty looks at the dried food. He's hungry and it shows. Trader puts his hand on the bag and begins to slide it away until Dusty stops him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DUSTY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wait...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dusty reaches inside of a satchel and pulls out a thick, leather book; takes a long, aching look at it; and pushes it towards the Trader.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TRADER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Giving up the faith?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Trader chuckles and tosses the book onto a pile of others just like it in a box behind the counter. We can now see that except for a few copies of the Quran, they are all bibles. And surrounding the box, is a pool of blood. We follow it's trail to see that it leads to the recently deceased body of a pale, older man. He is wearing a work apron that resembles one of a hardware store clerk, and has a single shotgun wound to the chest.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Trader Shop - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The air heavy with depression, Dusty exits the makeshift store cautiously and stuffs his purchase away in the satchel. We can clearly hear his panicked heartbeat again. He sees two men approaching the store. They look like land pirates. The only things they are missing are colonial hats with a skull and crossbones and a talkative parrot.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dusty picks up the pace in the other direction to avoid any confrontation, but these two look like they want to know what Dusty is carrying. He has almost broken into a full run when he rounds the corner of the building, looking back and (CRASH). Dusty falls. He must have walked into a wall. BUT IT'S MOVING. The sunlight on Dusty is covered by shadow as we see a behemoth of a man towering over him. He looks unreal. We can still only make out the giant's silhouette as a large excuse for a hand reaches down to grab Dusty by his neck. Dusty tries to run, but there is no where to go, as his feet kick helplessly in the air for some footing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Dusty drops to the ground and we get our first clear look at BEAST (a bearded man, wider than he is tall, looks as though he could charge a rhino head-first and win). He may never say a word, but his actions speak much louder. Dusty scrambles to get away, but the two pirates are right there to grab him, take his satchel and toss him back to Beast.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">It's the cruelest thing they could have done. For as large as he is, he moves well. Dusty trying to get away the entire time, is grabbed by Beast who takes him under his arm like a child with a stuffed animal, but he's probably cracking his ribs. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Beast slings the smaller man into the side of a nearby van that he bounces a few feet off of before a running Beast shoulders him back into it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Beast</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hold him up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The two men each grab one of Dusty's arms and stretch him out, forcing him to stand next to the van in front of Beast. Crouching down as if he's preparing for a football drill, the hulking man powers himself forward crushing Dusty like an oncoming train.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see the van shaking from the other side with every crushing blow. After the vehicle has shaken for an uncomfortably long series of barrages, we see the scene from across the lot, near the entrance to the trade shop.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A man walking, mostly just an outline, moves through the frame as the camera is now following his actions. He glances over at the land pirates picking up the limp body of what used to be Dusty, but never breaks stride as he enters the shop. Beast notices him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. TRADER SHOP - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan, (in his 30's now, bald with a beard, weathered and dressed like he's been left over from some war he volunteered to fight) takes off his dark goggles and makes his way around the shop. He stops in an inconspicuous aisle and takes a crumpled, torn paper from his pocket. It's a list. Trader, curious, leans over and takes a look at what Jagan is doing. Jagan can feel the prying eyes and stuffs away his list, grabbing seemingly random items. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A barrage of things hit the counter this time. Wire cutters, batteries, a flashlight, seeds, tape, a spoon, etc. Trader looks confused.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">TrADER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So... What's your trade?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan looks at him and almost begins to smile before we.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. TRADER SHOP - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan exits. His bag full, walking at a healthy pace. The same path as Dusty. The pirate sidekicks are circling around. Jagan nears the corner of the building but suddenly stops. He takes his bag from his shoulder and places it on the ground neatly beside him. He waits.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Out steps Beast. With confidence on his face and bloody knuckles, he strolls toward Jagan. But Jagan doesn't wait. He strolls toward Beast but his last few steps become lunges as he slides into mountainous man, going for his legs first. He seems to be punching him in the knees and Beast swings at him, but Jagan intercepts his arms with every strike, somehow stopping the blows. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Beast looks to be in shock as Jagan now let's loose a barrage of chain punches to his torso. Beast seems unable to move. Jagan finishes with a blow to the neck, just below the jawline that stays in place. Beast's face is frozen, mouth open.  We pan from his face to the fist still firmly planted beneath the beard on his chin.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan slowly pulls out his fist and backs away, breathing heavily. Beast stands there, in total shock. The men look back at Jagan, as we now see the culprit. Affixed to the back of each of Jagan's gloves is a single blade, now dripping with Beast's blood. Deep red spills from his neck and he drops to his knees first and then tumbles the rest of the way to the ground. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is already sliding his bag back over his shoulder, and in a voice that sounds like a whisper in your ear that could fill a room, he speaks for the first time in this world.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Is that your truck?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan motions over to a dirty, heavy duty red pick up that the men had been hanging out at.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Open road - eVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Wheels of the red pick up traveling down a deserted road kick up dust clouds. We see a quick shot back in the shop of Trader behind the counter on the ground beside the old man. We can't tell if he's dead or simply unconscious, and we're right back to Jagan driving as we begin to hear his voice.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(OPENING CREDITS)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">These runs are never easy. And necessity brings out the cruelness in men. There were signs that this was coming, but no one pays attention until it's too late. It was 2018 when the fish began to die. Anything farm raised or genetically modified in the waters was dead in weeks. Next came land animals, then crops... Major food shortage. We almost went to war for more, but it was a worldwide phenomenon. And it was about to get worse. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Hero house - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan's voice is still heard as he parks and covers the truck, surveys the landscape, repairs the fence, etc.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The last human child was born in March of 2020 and died a few weeks later. Women stopped being able to conceive, and then came the Blue Death. It took no prisoners. No favorites. When the symptoms begin you have two, maybe three days at best. First it took the children, then the elderly... then the women. All of the women. Men died by the millions, but with no women left... Hope died too.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is now in the house getting cleaned up, washing and chopping vegetables, preparing a meal. He brings a large beautifully prepared plate with him and walks to an area in the house brandishing an incredible floor to ceiling tapestry. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The cloth has beautiful colors and designs and Jagan seems almost hypnotized and takes a glance around as if to secure the area. Jagan then pulls back on one side of the piece to reveal a door which he opens and starts down the stairs into the basement. We see the door close and the cloth reset behind him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The left over military and police of the world have morphed into a set of small groups called ONE FORCE. While we try to hold on to what's left of life, they have scientists trying to re-create female life in labs. They've also been on an unofficial militarized witch hunt, where people say they are wasting their resources looking for what no longer exists...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. BASEMENT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan steps into the basement which is an organic oasis. There are pastels everywhere, fountains and flowers, plants, fruits, paintings, and silk sheer fabrics. Finally, we see HER silhouette. This is the first beauty we've seen in this harsh world.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But I know something that they don't... there's one left.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">For the first time we see Ma'at as an adult, reminding us of her mother. She looks like a young Queen, brown and natural, head held high, age impossible to guess (as if it mattered). They look at each other as if they've been forced apart for years. She runs to him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Jagan..</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Basement - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">In a candle lit portion of the room, Ma'at and Jagan sit in a corner that they've made into a cove, intimately eating from the same plate.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And did you get the seeds I put on the list?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">Some of them. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(Off her look) </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Some may not even exist anymore, Ma'at... But I did find a truck with some fuel and ammo.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Find?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Aquired.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(off her look)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Which is how I was able to make it back a day early.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at softens. Jagan is right. This trip should have taken longer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I've missed you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You've always had me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at moves and turns to face him. She places her hand on his chest and reveals...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You're burning.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan takes his time as he always does with her, searching himself first, to answer with sincerity.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">For you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at grabs Jagan's hand and places it on her breastbone. He's a bit surprised at first and then awed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You're not the only one who burns.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan grabs her and draws her in for a kiss that feels new, even for two who have done it countless times. They melt into moments of intimacy that exceed normal connections. In a claw foot tub lit by candles he washes her; she shaves his head and tends to his wounds, he reads to her, kissing her all the while as we explore this oasis that is the basement. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">As time passes we notice that a candle has burned to almost nothing and we leave its fleeting flicker to cross the face of Ma'at, sound asleep. Jagan's arms tighten around her and we land on his face. Troubled.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. BASEMENT - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan places a kiss on Ma'at, careful not to wake her, before he rises and proceeds up the stairs. Ma'at, eyes closed and peaceful, sheds a silent tear.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can't stay. I can't let my guard down. Ma'at is the most precious thing in this world...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan takes a cloth and a pail of brownish water and begins to put it over himself. He then puts on layers of clothing that are dusty and unkempt as he explains.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And with any moment of negligence, that world could be over. So for that, we can only visit our life together. We cannot walk outside and feel the sun or the wind or the rain. I cannot smell like her. And I cannot speak of her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan lies atop a bed in a drab, dusty room with only a wooden chair as furnishings. He holds a rifle across his chest as he stares at the ceiling.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I must always be ready. Because of what I know... </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We can hear a buzz that progressively grows louder. Two "One Force" drones fly by in the night sky.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">One day, they'll come for her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see a shot of Ma'at sleeping peacefully in the basement.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But they cannot have her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - MORNING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The room once lit by moonlight is now in an orange hue. Jagan's rifle is on the bed in the same position, but there is no sign of him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int/Ext. HERO HOUSE - mORNING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A view of the orange sunrise over the fields peeking between the trees and moisture on a spider's web, lets us know how early it is. We see it's from Jagan's POV as he peers through the living room window. He moves around inside the house from all vantage points, checking the perimeter. Drops of sweat hit a wooden floor as we reveal Jagan is now full on training. Difficult stretches and balance positions, push ups, handstand pushups, pull-ups, speed work with a wooden dummy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">He then heads outside to an area behind the house and moves some mesh metal fencing and downed branches that have been concealing solar panels. Jagan takes an old rag and wipes off a layer of dust that has no doubt been making it difficult for the panels to be very effective. He walks up to a back patio and checks on a small potted bush that appears to have tangerines growing on it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan inspects the plant, brings it inside.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - Basement - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A drop of liquid hits a glass frame underneath a microscope. Ma'at is in botanist mode. This is her world. Her twisted, dark locks of hair are pulled back as she concentrates on her tasks. We see Jagan walk up from behind her with the bush, but she doesn't seem to notice until he moves her hair and plants a kiss on the back of her neck.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(referring to the plant)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I think she's ready.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at see's the plant and is immediately giddy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">She's responding really well to the new food. I'm going to take some samples before you take her back up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan leans in closely to see what Ma'at is jotting down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And I fixed the blade on your right glove.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(off Jagan's look)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It was getting stuck. Whatever you hit with it this time bent the frame.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan has a split-second flashback of his final blow to Beast during their fight, as he handles the gloves, maneuvering the blade. It works perfectly now. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Musta hit a tree or something.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at continues to work as she speaks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yep. Or something.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Changing the subject, Jagan walks over to something he hasn't seen before; a painting on an easel.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You started on a new one? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at doesn't seem to have really wanted Jagan to discover this painting.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This is you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at shakes her head, "no". A reveal of the painting shows land during sunrise and the silhouette of a woman with flowing locks, arms outstretched, facing the light. The shadow of her on the ground clearly depicts a tree.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Your mother?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's all of us. It's life. Conspiring.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And what is it conspiring?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Immortality.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(understanding)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Through life cycles. By creating more life, we live forever.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at nods. Jagan always knows more than he lets on. She releases a few drops of a green liquid into the soil around the tangerine bush and steps aside for Jagan to have room to grab it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. Let's take her back up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan grabs Ma'at instead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Beautiful... a botanist who paints and repairs weapons... If you could cook, you'd be the perfect woman.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">POW! Ma'at play punches Jagan in the arm, but he reacts as if he just got slugged by a heavyweight boxer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(playfully)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's what I've got </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">you</Text>
<Text Style=""> for. I AM the perfect woman.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes. Shit. Yes you are. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">AVEE, a furry brown Dachshund comes running around the corner barking.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'll take her up with me and we'll check on the other trees.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Good.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at looks over at her freshly painted work.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">At least one of us will get to see the sun.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan feels the pain behind her words, but they can't risk her safety. There's always someone watching.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From the POV of a ONE FORCE drone we see the property of Jagan and Ma'at from high above. We now get a clear view of the drones and how they are affixed with small mounted cameras.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. One force compound - gunny's office - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see on a flat-screen, a grassy area. Amateur camera work. Soon it becomes clear that we are looking at a horse stable and GUNNY, a leathery 50 something year old man who feels as though he's been in war every day of his life. And loved it.  In these recordings however, he feels like a very different man. He's helping his ten year old daughter, WINNIE get settled on a horse for the first time, giving her the assurance she needs. His wife, MORGAN, 30's a military housewife in a sundress and cowboy boots looks on and participates. They all take turns making faces at the camera. The present day, more mature, hardened Gunny watches as if he's hoping to find something that he hasn't seen before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny leans close to the screen, clearly moved. In the video, Morgan is also consoling Winnie.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Morgan (video)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's ok, baby. It's a nice horse. You don't have to be scared. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny (video)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Winnie. What is fear? Come on, tell me what is fear?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(turning to the camera)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Phillip, turn that off.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The camera pans down for a second and then goes back up to frame Winnie atop the small horse and zooms in on her face as she contemplates speaking up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Looking back at present day Gunny, we see him mouthing along to his own words in the video.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny (VIDEO)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You know. Fear is...?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Winnie (viDEO)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(in her small voice)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fear is... dread for something that may not even happen.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY (VIDEO)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fear is...?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">WINNIE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Weakness.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY (VIDEO)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Good girl. Now breathe.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The little trooper takes a few deep breaths and shakes out her tiny hands.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny (VIDEO)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. Now let's ride.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Younger gunny begins to back away to make room for her to command the horse when.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">KNOCK KNOCK! JACKSON, (30's soldier, buzz cut) Gunny's second in command, walks in and begins speaking right away.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jackson</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hey, Gunny. We got three ready for trials--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">FWACK! A blade is in the wall next to Jackson's head, clearly thrown by Gunny. Jackson touches his fingers to the side of his head and discovers a fresh cut on his ear beginning to bleed. Gunny stands as he speaks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There are no more officer ranks. So, are you a Master Sergeant?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jackson answers, although a bit confused.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Are you a First Sergeant?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No, Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Sergeant Major?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No, Gunny?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny seems genuinely confused. He's not.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Did I invite you into my office?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">No response.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Did I. Invite you into my office?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No, Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Then why are you here?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I came to tell you that there are--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You misunderstand me... Get out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jackson nods and backs through the door closing it behind him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny sits down and turns his attention back to his video, which is now paused on the face of Morgan. Moments pass before there is a timid knock at the door. Gunny takes his time and closes the screen before responding.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Come in.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jackson enters quickly, albeit much more cautiously than before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JacKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There are three recruits that made it through endurance trials, Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Three? Shit. Guess it's time to make em' harder.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. One force compound - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A small crowd of One Force soldiers in uniform surround three young men who are prospective new members of the outfit. The exterior of the compound is drab like the rest of this world. A clearing next to the treeline seems to be the focus of where the action takes place.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The prospects are stretching and trying to stay loose for what may be next. We see SQUAT, a twenty something year old that looks like a stocky college football player. MANTIS, a lean, shifty eyed young man with a Muy Thai background. The last one we see is KID, (19, brown-skinned with medium length locks and tattoos on his arms and chest) who is the first to notice Gunny and Sergeant Jackson approaching.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">As Gunny nears the crowd, it gets noticeably quiet and more orderly. He barely looks at the young men before speaking.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well done. Well done. These are not easy trials... and they've claimed the lives of more than a few. But to be in the ranks of humanity's last hope, is not supposed to be an easy job. We are the last line of defense against extinction, and disorder... and it takes a strong will and an iron hand to keep order and control in a land of men without Gods and kings. Here, we are one mind. One body!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">All of the One Force soldiers chime in unison.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">One force soldiers</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">One Force!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And that's not to be taken lightly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(looking at the prospects)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do you understand?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Prospects</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(not quite in unison)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes, Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny looks a little perplexed and walks up to Kid who barely gives eye contact.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sarcastically)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Sergeant Jackson. Is this, Kid?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes, I believe it is Gunny. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So you made it through the trials, Kid?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And he had the fastest time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No shit? Well dammit I'm impressed, boy. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You're not still stealing are you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No, Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny looks Kid and the others over and nods his head, walks a few feet away and turns back to them after some thought.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">In times past, completing the Endurance Trials was enough to secure a spot in our training program. This is no longer the past. And unfortunately at this time... there is only one spot available.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">One of the soldiers brings Mantis and Kid mouthpieces and headgear. It appears that Squat will have to wait until the next round. The two young men square up for a fight with Kid raising his fists and bouncing around like a boxer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Sergeant Jackson. Does One Force use training pads on the job?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JACKSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No Gunny, we do not.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A couple of soldiers step up to grab the helmets and mouth guards from Mantis and Kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Now let's make this fast.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Mantis comes swinging full force at Kid. He's sloppy and Kid dodges his attacks. Kid is a better fighter and more controlled, but Mantis has long arms and legs that are hard to get around.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm getting bored. You realize, I don't actually </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">have</Text>
<Text Style=""> to accept any of you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">With this new motivation to get the job done, Kid charges forward and lands a spinning front kick to the head of Mantis, knocking him out cold. The crowd reacts to the knockout as if it were a championship match. Kid is pleased with himself and looks to gunny for approval when-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">WHACK! A board breaks across the back of Kid's head, sending him to the ground. The culprit is Squat, who now grabs a woozy Kid by his collar and gives him one more punch to the face for good measure. Kid collapses in pain.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny walks over and stands above Kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Gotta know your enemy. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(to the soldiers)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Looks like we have a winner. One mind. One body.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">ONE FORCE SOLDIERS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">One Force!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Let's get them out of here and start training fresh meat here in our--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Soldier (O.S.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">-Gunny!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A soldier comes running at full speed and out of breath.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SOLDIER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We might have a hit!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Female?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SOLDIER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(nodding)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Possibly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny moves quickly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. One force compound - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny, Jackson and the third soldier (We'll call him Tech) look at a screen showing footage from one of their drones.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Tech</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You see that? Now watch what he goes back to grab....</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From our vantage point we can't see the screen, but Gunny ponders for a second.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Tech</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(pointing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There. Now, it could be nothing. But it also-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Could be everything...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(to Jackson)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Load the boys up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny rushes off and off Jackson's face we:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. HERO HOUSE - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Avee emerge from between trees with a branch of avocados and a satchel of various other fruit. They soak up the sun as Avee gets some play time in.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. ONE FORCE SUV</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Inside of the lead SUV we see the looks on their faces as Gunny and a few men are speeding down a dirt road. A close up reveals the fire in Gunny's obsessed eyes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan opens the back door to his home and just before he goes in, he looks around as if it seems there is something not quite right in the air. He pulls the door securely shut behind him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">BOOM! BOOM! BOOM! A One Force soldier's fist bangs on a door. The reveal shows Gunny giving the head nod "okay" to kick the door open. CRASH! The door is breached with one kick and armed men fill the home like rushing water as yelling is heard!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">JOHNSON, another soldier is inside yelling commands.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JOHNSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Get on the ground now!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">By the time we reveal Gunny rounding the corner and landing inside, we see Johnson's knee is already in the back of SAGE, a tall lean man of Middle Eastern decent with a thick beard. Sage is a fast talker who seems quite surprised.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Sage</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What the fuck? What the fuck? Take what you want!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GunnY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh we will.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Avee lounge on the couch, having quiet unbothered moments. This time, they are not the targets.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. Sage's house - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(to Johnson)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Let him up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sniffing the air)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I smell perfume...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson stands Sage up to his feet.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GunNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do you know who I am?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage looks around at the men first and then nods his head.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And so you know what I'm looking for don't you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage reluctantly nods his head again. Gunny gets right next to Sage's ear.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Take me to her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage, begins to break down and cry as Johnson stands him upright and they walk towards a back room that he half-heartedly leads them to. The door is closed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JOHNSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Open it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage has given up hope at his point and opens the door to reveal a pink room, decorated like it's for a little girl. Dresses, sun hats and dolls are everywhere. From the reverse angle we see the back of a chair, and long hair flowing off the side of it. Gunny steps full frame into the room to see the female figure sitting in the chair. It's a full sized sex doll, completely outfitted like a real woman. Gunny is confused and turns to Sage.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where is she?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage looks at Gunny shaking his head. Gunny's patience for games has long worn off. He grabs Sage by his jawline and uses it to hold him against the wall.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Enough games. You're gonna tell me where she is.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage is still a crying mess and half-heartedly motions over to the doll as he struggles to speak.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Sage</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">She's right there!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny releases him and walks around the room; opening the closet and looks back at Sage who is beginning to gain his composure.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SAGE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Right there. In the chair. In her favorite dress.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">A fucking doll?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men are visibly disappointed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SAGE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">She's all I got. Please.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny is not pleased one bit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Load up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The soldiers begin to file out of the house and back to the trucks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So you were bringing women's clothing into your house... to dress this doll?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SAGE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes. Trish doesn't like to wear the same thing too many times.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny understandingly nods his head.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nobody does.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From his leg holster in a flash, Gunny pulls his handgun out and POW! There is a fresh bullet hole in the head of Sage's doll, still smoking.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SAGE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nooooooooooooo!!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Sage runs over to Trish and grabs his doll as if she's in need of actually being saved, and collapses in a crying heap with her in his arms. Gunny walks out of the room and Johnson looks on at Sage.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JOHNSON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(to himself)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Now that's just mean for no reason.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Ext. SAGE's house - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We can still hear Sage's muffled cries as the One Force personnel load into their SUVs. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is quietly closing the door to the basement and resetting the tapestry. He performs his nightly ritual of checking the perimeter in the distance and securing all doors and windows before we see him again, in the bed of that simple room. Rifle in hand. More awake than asleep, keeping a promise he made to a man years before. In Jagan's eyes we see deep thought.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. RAY AND MAHI'S HOME - HALLWAY - 2021</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray and Jagan are as they were. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Things are gonna get worse before they get better. It's a good drive to where you're headed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yeah, I know. But at least we're not traveling alone. There's a guy from my old RECON unit that's meeting us on the road with his family.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray ponders this a moment, concerned.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do you trust him?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">With my life.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray gives Jagan all the weight of the world with his next question.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But do you trust him with </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">her</Text>
<Text Style=""> life? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The only other person I trust with her life is standing right here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray nods his head. Gives Jagan a strong hug.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm counting on you. Protect Her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I will, Ray.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE OUT.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Hero house - MORNING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is on the bed in the same position. His eyes pop open for no apparent reason, then we notice the sound of footsteps and Jagan disappears from the room in an instant as if he had never been asleep.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">KNOCK KNOCK</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - Front Door - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Before a third knock, Jagan opens the door to reveal Kid, now with a fresh black eye, who is taken aback by how fast Jagan was at the door.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Woah. Were you already headed to the grounds? Can I come?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan notices drones approaching. He grabs Kid and puts him in a seat near the door.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Don't get seen.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fine.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(having no choice)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'll just wait here for you then.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan seems slightly bothered, but also like he expected this. Kid gets up and peers around a corner. He's got a much lighter energy about him today than before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hey where's your---</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan grabs Kid and sits him back down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wait. Here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Bathroom?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan walks off, leaving Kid to sit alone with his thoughts a moment.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So, I'll just wait here, then. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can hold it. I think I can hold it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. OPEN ROAD - MORNING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Kid are jogging, military style along an open road. Kid is holding a one way conversation between his breaths.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">...So I told them that the drones One Force uses can pick up heat signals now and operate completely from AI. But they say it doesn't matter because we'll all be dead before they find a woman they can use to reproduce anyway...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan, annoyed with Kid just keeps jogging.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The Blue Death has already killed most of us and the last wave has already started. They say if they find one, they won't even try to mate her... they'll just take her eggs and incubate em. But we all know what they did to the last ones they found. You almost hope they don't find anymore... and how come you don't get tired?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Ext. Training course - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan slows to a walk as they have arrived at an outdoor obstacle course.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I was just thinking the same thing about you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">(CRACK) A target drops and we see this is a makeshift range and training ground hidden in the woodline left from some old military installation. (CRACK) Another target drops. From a secluded location, we see McConnor (now late 30's Irish with a red beard, tattoos and a heavy dose of "I kick-ass" about himself) emerge from his shooting spot. The years have been harsh for everyone.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McConnor</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Been a while. Thought you might have turned blue.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Not yet. Had to make a run. Thought you might've joined One Force.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So I can help them find the last skirts and then give them away? Fuck that. I find one, I'm more likely to shoot them soldiers in the face and keep her myself. Why you making so many runs out there?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan studies him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ran outta toothpaste. Found something for you too.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan reaches in his pocket and hands a large toothed comb over to McConnor.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fuck is this?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's a comb.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I know it's a comb. Fuck's it for?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Keeps that shit you talk from getting stuck in your beard. Stinks after a while.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid reacts to the jab from Jagan. McConnor uses the comb on his beard as the men laugh.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well, I've been looking for one of these.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men make their way to the start of the obstacle course and remove excess gear. It's a competition. Kid assists. We can tell that he is a fan of the skill level of these two gladiators. Kid stands off to the side as they line up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(in his best announcer voice)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Are you ready! Behold! A clash of warriors like you've never seen before? A spectacle of greatness!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and McConnor shake their heads at the loud youngster, but both dig in. Neither man likes to lose.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KiD</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's time! Hold on to your hats!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid holds up a piece of cloth like it's a flag.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">On your marks. Get set. Get ready. Almost time!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Kid!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Go!!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid's antics distract Jagan momentarily and McConnor gets the head start as the men run through their objectives. The obstacles cause them to have to pull their bodies up ropes and dive under logs, maneuver walls and shoot targets. In the end, both men breathing heavily, look at Kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Too close to call. It's a tie.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There's no such thing as a tie.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No ties.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Sooooo. You gonna run it gain?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Both men look over at Kid like he's lost his mind.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh, right. Targets.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Target area</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men are now looking at a dummy cutout target. It's maybe 25 yards away. Jagan checks his ammo. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What do ya say we make it interesting?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor pulls out a knife from his side and begins to twirl it in his fingers. Kid gets excited. Jagan dramatically backs up, giving him room to throw.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor sets and throws. The knife whips through the air and lands almost dead center mass in the chest area of the body cut out. McConnor is deadly and he knows it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You, uh... need to borrow a knife?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan grabs a knife from Kid's holster and without setting, launches a blade to the target. It lands between the eyes of the target, dead center. The knife is still vibrating from the force as we focus on a lion head molded into the tip of the handle. Kid is speechless.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nope. That one's fine.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Kid retrieve his knife. Kid looks at it as if it now possesses magical powers.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's not even a throwing knife.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's whatever you make it. And don't ever let anyone take it from you again.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan walks off leaving Kid alone with his thoughts. In the distance, McConnor is still not happy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Any day you get done yanking' his meat how about you bring me my fuckin' blade, Kid?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A beat.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And I was aiming for the heart by the way. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What kinda asshole throws a knife at a man's face?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid and Jagan are there, walking back from training. Kid never shuts the fuck up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Personally, I think he's got real psychological issues. Like, you know he eats everything he catches raw, right? Did you know that?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan looks at a single drone buzz by overhead as they walk.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And I don't mean, "oh, he cleans it and eats the meat". I mean this dude eats the blood, the bones, the feathers, the beak--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You can't eat a beak, Kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">THAT'S what I thought. But he would eat the beak, bro! That's why I can't let him train me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Now Jagan is right at his fence about to go home. Kid gets in front of Jagan, blocking his path in order to get his attention.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So, I need you to do it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Do what?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Train me. So I can join One Force.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan almost doesn't know what to say.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Kid. With everything you know about One Force... And you know a hell of a lot... Why would you want to join them?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid hesitates.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Because... They still have everything. Water, food whenever you want it-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Is that where you got that black eye?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid's body language gives away the truth. Jagan let's out some frustration. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You need food, I'll show you how to get food, grow food, your own food.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And they're a group. They got each other's back. I was twelve when my mom died. I've been making it ever since, but I'm tired. I just wanna belong somewhere.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan listens to him. Thinking about his next move.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I know you do, Kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Tory.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KiD</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">My real name is Tory. But I'm younger than everybody now so they always call me, "Kid".</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan takes all of this in before speaking.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Okay, "Tory". I'll train you. But not for One Force. I'll help you get what you need to stand on your own two feet. What you do with that is up to you. Deal?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid/tory</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes, Jagan. Deal! </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A breeze brings a familiar smell to Jagan's nose. He looks at the house, and has to cut the visit short.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid/tory</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'll bring some things over in the morning-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Next week. And we'll meet at a training ground. Not here. Got it? Not here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan ushers Kid away.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">KID/Tory</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Next week?.. you got an extra gun?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes. Next week, go home kid.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid notices the fragrance in the air.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid/tory</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You smell that? It's like-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Go home, Kid. Yes, I'll bring you a gun but you have to go now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid, slightly confused but more ecstatic about his upcoming training, starts down the road.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kid/tory</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Okay, next week. I'll be ready, Jagan.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan makes sure that Kid is continuing down the road before he turns his attention to the house. Kid wasn't yet a man who wanted to be called by his name when he was in contact with a scent like that before, but Jagan knows exactly what it is. And what that means.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Off a close up of jagan's face we...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. BASEMENT - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is knee-deep in work, a scientist's concentration. She's got a pen in her hand and is recording the results of some liquid inside of the beakers that line her countertop. Jagan enters and she is beaming with excitement. Ma'at begins to show him what she's been working on, but oblivious to her in her excitement, Jagan is clearly bothered.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I did it. When I broke down the timelines it became very clear to me how it spreads and why they couldn't trace it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You were upstairs today.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">If you look at the samples I took from these plants that are less than six weeks old--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You were upstairs today.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What? Oh, yes. I had to get something.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What did you have to get that couldn't wait until I got back?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Excuse me?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What amazing thing upstairs, in this house is worth your life? I could smell you from outside before I hit the porch.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is in shock and begins to get defensive.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This is my house also!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What if it wasn't me? What if it was Kid? What if it was McConnor?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Aren't those your friends?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We have no friends in this world! None. Any of them or all of them would come for you. Every three hours One Force drones pass through here like clockwork looking for you. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They're looking for any women.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There are no more women! I haven't told you this but they haven't found another one alive in over a year. Ma'at you are probably... you could very well be... the last living woman on Earth.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">This lands on Ma'at hard.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And you think this is living? I'm a prisoner. In the basement of a house that WE picked out. I need the sun, Jagan. I need the rain. I need to breathe air that hasn't passed through a vent before it touches my lungs. Look at me! Do you think this is "living" to me?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm just trying--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Trying to what?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Protect you. Keep you safe. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What's the difference between keeping me safe, and keeping me prisoner? Do you even know anymore?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is at a loss for words.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Your food is upstairs. I've already eaten. I will not be needing your company tonight. It's not like you stay anyway.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">On those stinging words, Ma'at walks away. She pulls closed a silk sheet that hangs in the center of the room. More of a statement than actual privacy. We land on Jagan deep in thought.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int. BASEMENT - the Next morning</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The basement door creeps open and natural light pours in. Jagan lands. Ma'at peeks from behind the hanging fabric, then rushes to him and they embrace. It's been a long night for both of them.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm sorry, I know how much you do to keep me safe and I just--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan quiets her softly with his hand.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You were right. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Grabbing Ma'at by the hand, Jagan leads her from the basement to a breakfast meal he's prepared at the kitchen table with plenty of sunlight filling the room. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Tears of joy say it all. She needed this. They eat breakfast together and laugh, even spend time on the back porch with her brown dachshund, Avee (who we've only seen in the basement until now) running about. It's been the most beautiful of days. They both needed this. On a couch near the window, Jagan holds her as her face soaks up the sunlight that she has been missing. They fall fast asleep on the couch.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HOSPITAL ROOM - MORNING - 2004</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A seven year old Ma'at lies in a lone hospital bed. Her breathing is being assisted by a machine. She has brown skin and wild, curly hair. Her parents are just outside of the room talking to doctors as Ma'at's mother, Mahi (now a botanist in her early 40's) slips away to sit beside her. She speaks softly to the sleeping child.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at. They say your lungs are weak, honey... It hurts to breathe doesn't it? But no matter how much it hurts... Never. Stop. Do not ever stop breathing baby.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The EKG machine and breathing apparatus are still going, and our view migrates over to the child. Her eyes are still closed. In the hallway we can hear the doctor talking to a younger, longer haired Ray as Mahi still sits by her daughter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Doctor</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">...and she seems stable one minute, but the next minute the assisted breathing doesn't help and her fingertips turn blue. At that point, she's clinically dead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ray</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's momentary, and it clears up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DOCTOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Momentary death? Ray, my concern is that we just haven't seen this before. This isn't asthma. This is something else. I've decided to call in a few specialists. They're on the way to see her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You mean study her. I'm a botanist. I know how this goes. It's called the medical "practice" for a reason. You're still "figuring" it out. And you're not figuring it out on her!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DOCTOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The insight we're getting from your daughter's condition could be very valuable in the future.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Mahi shoots Ray a look. They will </Text>
<Text Style="Italic">not</Text>
<Text Style=""> be experimenting on her daughter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No one is to see her or touch her without our approval.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">DOCTOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There might be something for all of us to learn here... regardless of the outcome.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Tensions have risen. To avoid a confrontation, the doctor walks away.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at. Ma'at. Baby. I need you to wake up now. They're coming.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We hear a vehicle pulling up outside. Mahi grows more desperate.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Come on, wake up Baby.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">(WHAM!) A vehicle door slams.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wake up!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Smash CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. HERO HOUSE - AFTERNOON - 2027</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">(WHAM!)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at's eyes burst open as the sound of more vehicle doors slamming jolts her and Jagan from their sleep.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The last door slams shut on a black Suburban SUV with the ONE FORCE logos on the sides. Gunny and two truckloads of his men hop out and survey the property.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Ma'at look at each other and...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Our mercenaries are casually approaching the front porch and Gunny stops to smell something in the air. He shoots a look to Jackson and begins to move purposefully up the stairs of the home and has one of his men knock on the front door. No answer. Gunny is not a man of much patience. He motions for a soldier to kick the door open. Just as the man is mid-kick, Jagan opens up the door appearing nonchalant.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Careful, buddy. You break, you buy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Was starting to think you weren't gonna answer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You could have just left a note.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wouldn't be much of a wellness check then, now would it?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well. I'm well. So, thanks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Staring contest as Jagan blocks the doorway. Gunny doesn't budge as the men tighten up on their weapons.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What IS that smell?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Must be the pancakes. I use a lot of cinnamon.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny begins to make his way in the house as Jagan reluctantly makes room for the men to pass by.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You must be hungry.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny enters the main area of the home peering around with suspicion. Jagan breaks the ice hoping to distract him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's a little early for a wellness visit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GunNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I decided to pay a personal visit to talk to you... concerning a position that recently "opened up".</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh yeah? Who died?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny motions to a chair in the living room.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">May I? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sitting)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We lost Sergeant Greene last week to the Blue. I'd like to see you take his place.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Greene was good. By good I mean, he was a piece of shit, but he was a fighter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You ever hear of a man they call "The Beast"?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Maybe... He's blue right? Fights in comic books?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(slightly amused)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No. This particular Beast is a land pirate. Heard he once ripped off a man's arm and beat him to death with it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Sounds like he's right up your alley.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yeah, well. Guess we'll never know. I was recruiting him, but before our appointment he met an untimely demise.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's what usually happens when someone slits your tendons and punctures your organs a few dozen times. They say the guy who did it had blades on the back of his gloves. Can you believe that shit?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan doesn't answer, so Gunny continues.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">As soon as I heard about the gloves with the blades, I thought of those rumors about you. What they said you did when you first got here. When some guys got close to your woman.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You looking for justice, Gunny?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I don't give a fuck about, Beast. I need someone who can continue the mission.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You've got plenty of soldiers who can take his place.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yeah. But I need the best.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">One of the soldiers accidentally knocks over a vase. Breaks it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">For obvious reasons.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm certain you've noticed. Humans are going extinct. There's not some great need for law and order anymore.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Which makes the search for the last surviving women so vitally important.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You still think there are more?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny stands and walks over to the tapestry that hangs over the basement door.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I KNOW there are more. I can feel it. The earth is just getting rid of the weaker ones so we can repopulate it with the strong.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So you want to find if any are remaining and harvest their eggs?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Harvesting didn't work on the last ones, and most of the scientists didn't make it. The next ones we find will have to get it as nature intended.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A couple of Gunny's men let out a chuckle.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So, if you're right and you happen to find the last living woman in the entire world; the possible savior of our race... your very next action would be to gang rape her? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan looks to Gunny and his men for a reaction. There is none.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Are you absolutely certain that you should be reproducing?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(turning to a soldier who laughed earlier) Especially you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The rules have changed, Jagan. Survival of the fittest. You telling me, you didn't start to feel more like a hunter when your wife died?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan looks up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">How long ago was that?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Gunny. I've already lost everyone. So if it's all right with you, I'd rather just live out my last few days right here. Alone.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Seeing a picture of Jagan and Ma'at on the wall, from a time when people used to take pictures; Gunny cocks his head to the side.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Jagan. How long ago was it that your wife died?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan notices a breeze from the basement causing the tapestry to move at the bottom. For our audience this happens in slow motion. He tries to step in front of it, but it's too late.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And what is that smell?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Shuffling can be heard distinctly from a back room. Gunny's eyes widen and he points his pistol at Jagan's head and sends two of the men to investigate.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Who else is here, Jagan? Have you been hiding something from me?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan doesn't answer or move. Gunny, moving eerily close to Jagan's face takes a deep, satisfied breath.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I knew I could smell it when I first walked in-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">(BARK) The sound of Avee barking interrupts Gunny mid-sentence. One of the soldiers has the small dog in his arms. Jagan rushes over and grabs her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Avee. What's wrong girl? She must be in heat. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(Jagan checks on Avee scratching behind her ears) </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wow. You guys really need a bitch, huh?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Off of the close up of Avee in Jagan's arms, we:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan walks with Gunny as the crew is loading back up in the vehicles.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Why would you have such a small, impractical dog?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JagaN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Had her since before "The Blue Death" started. Takes me back to the way things used to be.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan walks off, and Gunny pauses a bit. Waits until Jagan is out of earshot before giving Jackson instructions.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Have Tech double the drone times in this area. In case Jagan is doing more than just farming out here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int. BASEMENT - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan enters the darkness of the basement with Avee. Ma'at is fully dressed and waiting.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They're gone. But they'll be back.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. Do you know how much time we have?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan just shakes his head. Ma'at guides him over to her work area to explain what she's been trying to show him since the day before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well, we need to leave soon anyway. Everyone else is about to die.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes, we know everyone's dying.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But I know WHY they're dying. And I also know how much time everyone has left.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at makes her way over to her chalkboard, Jagan looks on.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So, contrary to what they said, Blue Death isn't random or untraceable. I've found out what's causing it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at sketches as she talks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This, represents the surface of the earth. And this, is our upper atmosphere.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A simple, effective drawing is emerging during her explanation.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">In that atmosphere, there is our air, which is more prevalent near the surface and gets progressively thinner as you rise. Plant life doesn't make the air, but it is what makes it more breathable.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">More chalk?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan hands her fresh replacements.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Thank you. So let's say, this point, at the start of our timeline, is the "Industrial Revolution". Here at the end is right now. It began with the big trees. Some of them began producing a compound in their sap that hadn't been noticed before. But now I'm finding that same compound in the skin of small plants that we've grown right here from seeds. It's in the air and the water.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What about the animals? They've been breathing and swimming in that same air. And they seem to be doing just fine.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Select ones. But farmed animals and fish died years ago. I think the plants are actually picking who they want to be able to breathe the air. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at goes back to her sketch.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It likely started many years ago, to combat the killing of the forests. Then it began filling up the atmosphere in high altitude places and probably reached sea level around 2018.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(realizing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It just got more concentrated. Meaning... the planet is literally exterminating us to survive.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at nods her head and takes her time before her next statements.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I still haven't pinpointed exactly why women are so much more affected.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Because women birth life. The first thing it did was make women sterile.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes. That's right.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">This is painful reminder for Ma'at, and seems to be an old wound for them.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at. How do you know all this? That it was in the trees? Why aren't you affected?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I am. Affected. But Blue Death has already killed me once.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Off Jagan's look we...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLASH TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Rustic kitchen - afternoon - 2004</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see young Ma'at at a wooden table with various supplies laid out. It looks like a child's tea set, but with leaves and jars of things she must have collected on her own.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<ScriptNote ID="1" Color="#000000000000" Type="" Name="" DateTime="20170328T194312">
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="3.88" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Revisit scientific mechanism of dilutions/titrations here. </Text>
	</Paragraph>
</ScriptNote><Text Style="">I've always wanted to be a botanist, just like my parents and I was excited to show them a tea I was making from the sap of a particular, very old Giant Sequoia. It was in that thick sap, broken down by the warm water and the leaves I steeped it in, that did it to me. I drank it from the source directly. What we're exposed to now, what we breathe, those are only titrations. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray comes in to find his young daughter, blue around the lips and fingers, unconscious on the floor.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HOSPITAL ROOM - MORNING - 2004</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see Mahi in slow motion, in the same position as she was earlier, telling Ma'at to wake up. The doctor and assistants come rushing into the room to try and stabilize her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'at (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They said I was gone for over two hours. But I remember everything like I was seeing it from the outside.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Mahi is holding the deceased hand of Ma'at. We see everything else as Ma'at is describing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I watched as my father balanced his time between fighting with the medical staff and consoling my mother... and I even saw him find his own space to grieve for me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see an inconsolable Ray, yelling at the pain of losing his daughter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But when I finally opened my eyes, I could breathe again.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The staff is walking Mahi out of the room and all have their backs turned when young Ma'at, back from the dead, steps out of the bed and speaks.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Young Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Mama? Don't cry. I'm ok now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FLASH TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. BASEMENT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You beat it?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No. I joined it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. HERO HOUSE - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan pulls the tarp and trees away from the top of the truck he's hiding on the property. Normally he'd walk, but time is of the essence. We hear the rest of the conversation between them from the basement as he works.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can't risk taking you out there.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And how long do you think I'll survive here without you? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at takes his hand, tenderly puts it on her face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Jagan. I need you. And I can already feel your temperature dropping. We have to go now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Exterior -Open road</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is in his truck barreling down the dusty road as we hear his journal entry.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at has always had an unexplainable connection to nature, an untouched fairy in a world of gargoyles... she wants us to find this tree that saved her... for me to drink its sap... breathe its air... she thinks it can save me too, but it might just kill me instead. It'll be a long trip, at least a day of driving. We'll need a map.. and fuel.. and I only know one person that can help me. A Priest.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Interior- Priest's place</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see Priest (40's, unkempt hair minister's collar on) behind the counter of what looks like a bar. Well, maybe it's just a ratty dark space that has found a way to pair liquor with sex dolls. There are sex toys on shelves behind the counter right with the bottles. There are two men at the counter trying to buy a pocket pussy, bickering with Priest over the trade. A giant man, Zeus (7 ft tall with an afro-mohawk and a chip on his shoulder) approaches and splits the two men apart with little effort. Zeus turns to the man at his right.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Zeus</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Pay.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The man hesitates. Zeus smashes the man's head against the counter and his body slumps to the floor. The camera focuses on a bloody gold tooth he left behind and racks focus to the other man staring at it. Zeus turns his attention to him, and without hesitation the man empties his pockets on the counter. A flashlight, a couple of batteries, some jewelry. Priest eyes the pile of goods.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Priest</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's not enough.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Zeus turns back to the man who quickly removes his jacket and hands it to Priest. Who grabs it enthusiastically.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh, this is a nice one.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest wraps the adult toy in brown paper as if he cares about customer service and slides it over the counter. Zeus picks it up and walks out, passing and eyeing Jagan who is making a b-line for the counter. Priest sees Jagan and runs from behind the counter to greet him. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Priest</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Jagan! Come here, man!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest reaches out for a hug, but Jagan stops him abruptly at arms length.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What's wrong?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where are your pants, Priest?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We realize that Priest is dressed like a minister from the waist up, but is wearing nothing else but "whitey tighties" and slippers.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Who needs pants? The whole world is like one big men's locker room.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest goes back on the merchant's side of his counter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Besides, you saved my life. We're like brothers!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Don't make me regret it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest pours a glass and slides it in front of Jagan.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Here's a water, since that's all you drink... and I will drink this shit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest pours himself a brown liquor. Jagan studies him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">When did you loose your faith?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(laughing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hell, I still got faith. But now... my faith is in me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest takes the shot he just poured to the head, and begins to pour another.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Whoo! Ok. When The Blue Death started and the people didn't have answers, they came to me... they confessed sins that ain't even sins in this world today. I gave them Hail Mary's to say, words of encouragement... and I prayed. And do you know what happened? What miracle took place because I vowed to live in the service of my creator? Nothing. They all died. The nuns were some of the first to go. When people realized that we couldn't save ourselves, they stopped coming. Deep down, I was glad. Because it meant I could stop lying. So one day, I packed up and left. And I didn't ask God, Jack Shit. That's when I realized... he couldn't stop me if he wanted to.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">If you could go back, do it all again... what would you change?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest thinks it over for just a second, before he gives his serious answer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'd fuck a nun.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is speachless. Priest laughs at himself before turning his back and sliding over a dildo on a shelf to make room for a bottle of whiskey.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hell, I'd probably try to fuck em' all!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JagAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Of course you would.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan eyes the room quickly before choosing his next words.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I need to take a trip. Maybe two days drive. I need a map and enough fuel.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Maps are hard to come by these days. Even I only keep one, just to point people in the right direction. Where is it you want to go?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan knows that Ma'at has to plot the course, so that won't work.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">A few places. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan brings out his bargaining tool. He's got a pair of Ma'at's red high heeled shoes in a sealed bag. Priest's eyes get big. Jagan breaks the seal open so he can get a whiff. Priest is overcome and reaches across the counter for them, but Jagan pulls back.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JagAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Map.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest lets out a sigh and brings out a heavily used atlas map of the area.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">One Force has taken control of most of the fuel, but I did hear about a tanker that was taken a while back. It's controlled by a nasty bunch. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(Pointing)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Here. Not an easy trip, my friend. And even if you can make it all the way there, they don't take many trades.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We'll work something out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan plops the shoes on the bar and walks out as Priest is sniffing the aroma from his new bag as if he's getting high. Completely oblivious to the world around him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut tO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. BASEMENT - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at looks at the map to determine where the big tree is, in relation to the fuel.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">The tree is here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You sure?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes. Only about a half day's drive from where we have to pick up the fuel.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can't take you with me to get the fuel.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(off her look)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">If they spot you it's all over, you know that. I'll come back for you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at pouts.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I think we should just take one trip. We don't have much time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No. If I'm not back in a day, head for the woods, and don't come back home. Keep moving until the rest die off.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at immediately smacks him across his face. Angry love.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No. You are my home. You come back. You always come back to me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan closes the distance between them as she halfheartedly backs away, invading her space. Angry love, retaliation. He kisses her. She jumps on him wrapping her legs around his waist. Passion. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - NIGHT turns into morning</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Priest's place - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest is pouring Kid a shot glass. Dark liquor. Kid is about to take the drink when Priest spies his knife, fastened to his hip.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">For that blade, I'll give you a whole bottle.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid takes the shot to the head. It burns. He can barely breathe.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Or maybe I can try to find you some milk and cookies instead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">In walks McConnor. People move out of his way. He must have a reputation. Even the kid slides off in a corner now that Jagan isn't there.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Father forgive me, for I have sinned.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No shit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest pours him a glass.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Planning to do a lot more too.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor laughs at his own joke with Priest.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You heard that they say a couple of women might be hiding in the far ridge?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nope. But I know One Force had drones and patrol going through there for months and didn't find shit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor doesn't like the news.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But I know you're going anyway.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor downs his drink.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Gotta keep the dream alive. If there is one, I'll find her before I die. I need you to show me a course.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can tell you roughly how to get there, but I gave the map to Jagan yesterday.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid is stashed away but he's listening intently to the conversation. McConnor is confused.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You gave away a map?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'll get another one. Just give me a few days. He seemed like he was in a rush to get outta here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">To go where?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Wouldn't say. But he was willing to make a good trade.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest pulls out the heels, proud of his new belongings. McConnor scoffs.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Shoes?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Not just shoes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest opens the bag and the aroma drifts out into the establishment. A few heads turn.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(excited)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You see how well preserved the smell is?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor's whole expression changes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's not well preserved. That's fresh.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's fresh! Son of a Bitch! She's still alive.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Who?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at. Fuckin' Ma'at...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor seems to be losing his mind right inside of the bar. More of the other patrons, including Kid, notice. Priest backs away.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And now he's trying to sneak her out of here before I find out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor's eyes have maddened. He downs his drink, pulls out a revolver and places it on the counter, looking at Priest.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I need ammo.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Priest is shocked and stoic.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm all out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor shoots him a crazed smile and pulls out a porn magazine, rolled up in a rubber band and a handful of jewelry that he plops on the counter. A generous offer. Priest looks tempted for a moment; then he recovers.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">PRIEST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(swallowing his breath)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I said I'm all out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor realizing the loyalty, packs away his belongings.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fine. I'll just do it the old fashioned way then.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">CLICK. We hear a side door close, and Kid is gone.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Priest's place</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kid looks frantic as he's exiting the building, speed walking down the dirt road.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int. PRIEST'S PLACE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">McConnor eyes the door and walks off. The men inside, including Zeus, all seem to have heard what is going on. Priest seals up his shoes, but doesn't seem quite as interested in them as before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. PRIEST'S PLACE</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see a close up of the knife the kid wears. A wider view shows him at a brisk pace down the road. Out of focus we see the Irishman exiting Priest's place eyeing Kid. Focused, McConnor lights a cigarette and begins walking in the same direction. Kid turns back to see him and picks up the pace. He has to warn Jagan. He has to tell him that they're coming for him. McConnor picks up his pace. Kid runs, McConnor runs. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SmaSH CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">KNOCK! KNOCK!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - EVENING</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan opens the door to reveal McConnor.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - Living room</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Focus is on the bottom of McConnor's boot as he puts out a cigarette butt. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So you came all this way to tell me that someone near the ridge might have put on a dress?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I thought you might be interested in going since you're planning a trip anyway, right?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan can feel the tension as the McConnor is prodding. Plays it cool.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Why not? Might as well see the world before it all ends.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's different. Most people think it already has. But you are in a unique situation. Aren't you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">At this point Jagan is just watching him. Waiting.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">A world without women is the ultimate test of manhood. It shows you who the fuck we become when there's no one left to impress... and do you know what we've become? Animals. Wild beasts whose only mission in life is to dominate and consume.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">How is that any different from the world before?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Before, we had someone else to live for... someone to protect.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan sees the kid's knife tied to McConnor's waist as he continues. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Everyone has changed, Jagan... except you... You still have this goddamn look in your eye like you have something to live for. Someone to protect. Now why is that?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The Irishman notices something on the couch by his hand... Picks it up. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">(Camera close up shows a single, long strand of Ma'at's hair in his hand. Focus racks back to Jagan.) </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Irishman treats the strand like a drug. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You know what I would do (runs the hair along his tongue) for that same feeling? Do you have any idea?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It doesn't matter... dead men don't reach goals.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">At that moment, both men lunge at each other and the first moments of impact are shown in slow motion.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">A drag-out fight ensues with many close calls that practically destroy the main living area of the house. In the end they are in a tug of war over the knife. McConnor has the upper hand. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MCCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You know that kid actually tried to reason with me when I finally caught up to him. I wasn't even gonna kill him. Until he tried to stab me... just to keep me from getting to you. Guess there is a little loyalty in this world.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">McConnor lunges at Jagan who grabs his arm and breaks it, taking the knife in the process. Jagan is now pressing the tip of the knife into McConnor's chest as he tries to push away with his one, good arm. It's a slow process as the knife struggles to sink through clothes, skin and bone. McConnor feeling his impending death has a few last words struggling out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">McCONNOR</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">There's more coming for her... how many will you kill, Jagan?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">All of them.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan uses his last push to jam the knife past McConnor's breastbone and into his heart.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">It was a tiring fight, but no time to rest. From the window he can see something in the distance.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CuT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int. BASEMENT - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan opens the basement door to see Ma'at standing there, worried.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">McConnor? I could hear him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No matter what you hear, stay down here. Grab what we need. I'll come back for you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I can load the truck--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There's no time. They're coming for you now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Who's coming?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan pauses, realizing the gravity of the situation.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Everyone.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Off Ma'at's reaction we...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Outside of the fence line we see a man crouched behind a tree loading bullets into a handgun. Behind a nearby tree we see another with a baseball bat. We remember them from Priest's Place. They must all know. As the shot pulls out we see no less than a dozen other men approaching in the moonlight, ready for a fight. Back to the first man. He's locked and loaded, animalistic look in his eye. Killer mode, he steps out. (CRACK!) A shot rings out and he drops dead. The second man is staring at him in shock and (CRACK!) The second man drops also.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is at the window. Rifle with a scope, (POW!) The sound is louder from the inside as we see him sniping the approaching men. The men begin rushing the house in small groups and Jagan keeps shooting them down. He gets maybe 5 or 6 more before they start getting much too close. As 2 kick in the front door he is right there, and the door area turns into a drag-out bloodbath as Jagan uses their own weapons to take them out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Camera angle from the outside shows an empty doorway as Jagan steps into full view. It's about to be a battle. Slow motion captures the action of him whipping out his hand blades for the first time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan sprints into the yard moving wildly taking out everything coming his way, until... We see 2 men vividly shaken by his viciousness, second guessing themselves... Is this a fight they are ready for? While one is making up his mind, his neck is snapped and his body thrown from behind by Zeus who emerges from the shadows. The second man runs away.  Zeus has a small ax in hand and we see Jagan gather himself.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">We see a POV from drones overhead catching the action. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. One force office - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Gunny in another location, eyes wide visibly crazed watching these events unfold.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Code Zero.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A few of his men look to be in shock and just look back at him. Gunny stands and calmly walks over to one of his soldiers who looks busy playing cards. In a blink, Gunny kicks the man's chair from under him and slams his head against the table, pinning him there.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Code. Zero.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men franticly begin running around gearing up grabbing weapons, including Johnson, the now bloody-nosed soldier who seems to be sporting a brand new bad attitude.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Zeus and Jagan spring forward and Jagan leaps in the air before being thrown several feet. This is not an easy fight. Several chokes, kicks, stabs and punches later, Zeus is finally bested by his own ax. 2 more men rush into the house amid his distraction and 3 more run in through the back door. A battered Jagan sees this, grabs the ax and rushes in.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CuT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. BASEMENT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is there, sweating, shallow breathing, rifle pointed at the doorway... Muffled noises from upstairs... shots, yells, things breaking, and then...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The door opens slowly at first, (she aims in, ready to fire) then snatches abruptly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Reveals a bloody, battered Jagan.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That wasn't so bad.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">He almost collapses as he says the words. She's so relieved she almost breaks down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Let's go.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">They begin gathering the items and both stop and turn at the same time as if they heard a noise...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. HERO HOUSE - NIGHT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Doors close on two black SUVs. It's the ONE FORCE. Heavily armed, they rush in looking through the destroyed house and find nothing. He notices a familiar smell and goes to where the mural tapestry is blocking the basement doorway. He rips it down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The men enter the basement in full tactical style. Gunny comes down the stairs. Looks around the basement. Nothing. Picks up a plant leaf. Turns to a soldier.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Put out a tracker drone.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Gunny slides a potted plant off of a shelf.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Camera POV sees the pot from below in slow motion. Just as it hits..</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. OPEN ROAD - dusk</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Ma'at and Jagan in their truck driving down a dirt road with lights off. They keep looking over their shoulders.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is looking at the map as Jagan drives. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We're getting close.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The truck rounds a bend in the dirt road and creeps to a halt. Jagan eyes the building in the distance. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's about a half mile away. I don't want to put you any closer. I'll bring the gas can we have and see if I can trade for another. Hopefully that'll be enough to get us there.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Can you bring me back some gum and dark chocolate?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan shoots her a look. She's almost happy to be out on a road trip again... even one that might kill them.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There's a gun here, ready to go... If you see anyone that's not me. Leave and don't look back. You have the map.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm not leaving without you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">She covers his mouth with her hand. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You better come back to me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Always.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan crosses the plane approaching what looks like an old gas station. The closer he gets, the more he realizes it has become a dusty hang out spot for drifters.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. Gas depot</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Everything is drab. No one seems to have anything better to do or a more important place to be... Many look close to death. Eyes yellow, fingertips purple and red, shallow breathing... these men are in their last days and they know it. There's nothing more dangerous or unpredictable than hopeless men.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan steps in with his gas can. A few heads turn, but most seem zombified as he walks through.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. Treeline - Jagan's truck - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">At the same time we see Ma'at back at the truck, growing uncomfortable already, anxious.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Int. GAS DEPOT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">A bearded man with long hair, (He'll remind us of a planet, so we'll call him Jupiter) and dark shades speaks up in his barrelly voice.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jupiter</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Looks like you want something.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Gas.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JUPITER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And what's it worth to you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan pulls out two avocados that Ma'at has grown in her basement greenhouse. No one has seen an avocado here since 2019 when international travel of all goods and services was stopped and the airlines were closed. He's holding pure gold. Jupiter reaches out toward the delicacy... Jagan pulls back, holds up the gas can. Jupiter grabs it and hands it to a skinny man.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JUPITER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Skinny Man. He wants some gas. Fill it up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jupiter nods at Jagan who gives him one of the fruits.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CuT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. TREELINE - JAGAN's TRUCK - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is shaking now and finally decides to step outside of the truck to use the bathroom in the tree line next to it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. GAS DEPOT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jupiter splits open the avocado with a knife, bites directly into it. Then we hear the distinct sound of liquid hitting metal. The skinny man is now peeing into Jagan's gas can. Jagan is not happy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. TREELINE - JAGAN's TRUCK - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is now finished and there is a gentle breeze. We hear an almost magical chime in the air as it brushes along her skin and follows a path toward the gas depot.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. GAS DEPOT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The gas can drops on the counter with a thud.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Skinny man</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Now.. I think it's only half full, but I'm all out. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jupiter and a few men laugh. Jagan grabs the can and turns to walk away. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh... your payment. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Skinny man has a nervous laugh, but with the audience he won't back down. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SKINNY MAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Toss it over.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Come get it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan holds out the green delight. Skinny man reaches out for it, but something about Jagan makes the man nervous and just an inch out of reach with his hands shaking he changes his mind.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SKINNY MAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Nah. You keep it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. Gas depot - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">We see a handful of men scattered about. Weary, zombified like on the inside... One sits, sharpening a blade. The breeze, the sound, a familiar smell from long ago. The man looks up, sniffs the air.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">InT. GAS DEPOT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">BOOM! Back inside, Skinny Man's back hits the floor and Jagan's boot is on his neck. Jagan lifts the urine filled gas can.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Okay, I'll keep it... but you gotta take this back.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan pours the contents onto the face of the skinny man who now struggles for air between gulps.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where's the gas?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">SKINNY MAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">There ain't no more gas!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Skinny Man manages to get the words out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JuPITER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">One Force took our gas weeks ago... Ain't nothin here but dying men.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan hits Skinny Man in the head with the empty can, knocking him out. Jagan takes a couple of deep breaths looking around the room and says. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You're telling me there's absolutely no gas?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jupiter puts down the rest of the avocado, fully expecting a problem, but an excited old man pokes his head in the depot and yells.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Old man</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They found a woman!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan's heart sinks. Jupiter pulls out a shotgun on Jagan. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JuPITER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I could smell her on you as soon as you walked through the door.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">BANG! There's a hole in Jupiter's chest and Jagan is already almost out of the door, gun still smoking.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. GAS DEPOT - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Word spreads fast and what seemed like a handful of zombies has quickly become over 20 animalistic, hunters... sniffing the air. One of them, the furthest from Jagan, Has spotted the truck in the tree line. We see the realization on the man's face and with no warning, he takes off.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Immediately, more take off. Full speed. Men that appeared to be on the verge of death are now in the race of their lives. Camera angle shows feet, but sounds like hooves. Overhead view shows Jagan, nearing the front, gaining ground, a man at war with the world.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">ExT. TREELINE - JAGAN'S TRUCK - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is fidgeting. She's trying to get in a quick nap. Completely oblivious to the danger that is a quarter mile away and closing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CuT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Open field</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">BAM! Jagan punches the closest man to him and he goes down in a tumble. Five more ahead of him, he doesn't miss a stride. The rest are harder to catch. He jumps on the back of of one and rides him to the ground, pops up and looks to run down the rest, but we can see the truck clearly now... He won't make it in time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan yells out to her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">He's too far away to be heard but...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Truck - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at's eyes open and she looks around without turning her head. She shakes it off and closes them again. But this time she hears her name clearly... </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN (O.S.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">She turns her head in time to see the first man's last few strides to her door. He grabs at the handle as Ma'at looks in horror as this crazed hillbilly raises his hand to break the window. BAM! Blood splatters against Ma'at's window as the man's body drops. Ma'at's shock is broken by a running Jagan, gun in hand, still 50 yards away yelling. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Drive!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at hops in the driver's seat and speeds off as Jagan is overtaken by the mob. She rounds a bend, checking the rearview and let's out a blood curdling yell.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Noooo!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">She stops after maybe a hundred yards, turns off the truck, pulls out the rifle and with her heart on her sleeve, she points the weapon at the approaching sound of the herd.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">As they draw closer she aims in, a warrior, standing her ground.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Seconds pass, yelling, we can see the figures through the trees. Now we look down her sights to see.. JAGAN! Ahead of the pack and running full speed. Ma'at can't believe her eyes as he yells. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Go!!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at hops back in and Jagan eventually catches up and jumps on the bed of the pick up as they zoom away from the mob. Happy tears down her face, and Jagan nearly passed out in the back, there's a moment of relief. Until we see a drone's POV and Gunny watching everything from a handheld screen in his own vehicle... In hot pursuit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They almost got my prize.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. OPEN ROAD - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Ma'at are outside of the truck on the roadside as he refuels the truck with the last of the gas from before.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I told you to leave me.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">She walks boldly to his face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And since when did I ever listen to you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Never. I should have told you to wait for me. You'd have been a hundred miles down the road by now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We don't have enough gas for that.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">See? I would never leave you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's because I'm the last woman on earth.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan closes the distance between them.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at, you were my only choice when there were five billion more...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The two LOVERS take in this brief moment of magic. But not for long. Jagan looks around in the air. Something's not right.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Let's get outta here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Door slams and the truck is off. From inside the truck we see Ma'at watching the countryside. A few drifters walking along the road are up ahead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You should stay down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You just want my head in your lap.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Off Jagan's reaction, Ma'at complies and we see the truck pass the strangers and go off down the distant road.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. Hallway - ray and mahi's home - 2021</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at takes her father's hand. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Did Mama put a spell on you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ray nods.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">RAY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Before you were born. Now go see her. She's waiting for you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at walks past the men in her life down a hallway leading to a sun room. Plant life is the decoration here as light pours in. In a chair, as queenly as ever, Mahi sits with her feet up beside her and a paintbrush in her hand. The canvass in front of her looks like an almost finished piece of work.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at walks in cautiously. The closer she gets, the more she notices her mother's normally bright lips are noticeably blue as are her fingertips as she takes frequent breaks between brushstrokes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What gives life?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at's eyes are filled with love and pain at the sight. Still standing in the doorway, she manages to answer.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Life is the giver of life. Everything in the universe conspires to make more life...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">By simply existing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at moves to her mother's side and curls up next to her as Mahi puts down her paint brush to comfort her daughter.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Mahi</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I got you something.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at perks up and sees a simple brown box on a low-top table. She picks it up and peers inside. Her heart melts.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I love him.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at pulls the gift from the box. It's an energetic little furry puppy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">It's a her, Baby.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well I love her, then Mama.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at cuddles with her new found joy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What's her name?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">That's between you and her to figure out. But I'm sure it'll be something special.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan knocks softly from the doorway with his knuckle.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm sorry. But they'll be closing up the roads soon and locking everyone down. We have to get moving.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Mahi</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Come here, Jagan.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan walks over and crouches down beside Mahi.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'm trusting you with my Baby, Jagan. You take care of her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan nods.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I will, Mama. Love you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Mahi</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Love you too.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan kisses Mahi atop her head and walks out.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">So they let them all out of the Army, permanently? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">He's a Marine, Mama.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Same thing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at shakes her head.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Not really... but yes, he's out. All of the militaries have shut down.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Good. You know you two are going to need each other right now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Yes.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You know your existing gives me life.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at struggles through her words.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Ma'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I just... I wish I could give you more--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MAHI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Shhh, shhh.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(squeezing her tightly)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh, Baby you did. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">For the first time we see a clear view of Mahi's painting and it looks exactly like the tapestry that covers the basement door.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at lays her head in her mother's lap for the last time and closes her eyes. Mahi strokes her hair. Unfamiliar male voices can be heard outside.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MahI</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at it's time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at doesn't budge. Jagan walks in.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JaGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">They're coming. We gotta move.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at still doesn't budge. It's as if she's in a coma.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A buzzing sound can be heard.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ma'at. Wake up, Baby. We've got company.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. OPEN ROAD - AFTERNOON - 2027</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at pops out of Jagan's lap from her dream.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I said, "We've got company".</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The buzzing is louder now and wee see a familiar sight overhead. It's one of the black drones from One Force trailing them, they can't be far behind.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at loads up a round into the rifle.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Drive straight.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We don't have much ammo left.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at gives him a wink.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From the drone's POV we can see Ma'at leaning out of the passenger window. She has a rifle in hand. POW! Screen goes fuzzy.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">INT. One Force SUV</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny's men are all looking at the screen, mouths wide open. They look at each other, then turn to him. Gunny turns off the device and. Puts it away. Fuming.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. OpEN ROAD - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan and Ma'at are driving past a particularly dense stretch of woods when the truck begins to stall.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Grab what you need and can carry. This is it for the truck. We'll have to leave Avee here for now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at thinks to protest, but just rubs her dog around her head and talks to her instead.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I'll be back for you.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The truck door slams and we see that they are leaving it on the roadside and making their way into the tree line. They are dressed like mercenaries, and for the first time in our story, Jagan is physically weak. He struggles with his large green bag and Ma'at notices that Blue Death is all over him. Jagan sees her looking but he just keeps trudging forward. He can't let her see him be weak. Not now.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Dirt road</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The One Force trucks slow to a stop as Johnson and Gunny step out. Now we see why. A drone, still smoldering on the side of the road from Ma'at's rifle shot. Gunny toys with it. He likes the chase.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(sotto)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Ok. You wanna play. I like to play too.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson reaches down to pick up the drone that Gunny is leaving on the ground.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Hell are you doing? You gonna fix it?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson looks at the drone that we see is damaged beyond repair. Places it back on the ground.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Top off the fuel. And the rest of you get ready. She shot a drone directly through the camera, eighty yards away, from a vehicle doing seventy down a dirt road. On her first attempt.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(to Johnson)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And you mutha-fukkas don't run that fast.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Deep in the forest</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan is using wire cutters to snip the end of a line he has hidden low between two trees. He quickly measures out the distance and buries two blades, point-up and covers them with leaves. He's moving with urgency. He snaps a branch and keeps moving. Talks to Ma'at as he works.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">What's left for ammo?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Six in the rifle. Didn't see anymore for the handgun.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan checks his .40 cal sidearm. Pops the magazine out, takes a peek and slides it all back where it came from.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Don't know how many are coming, but I've never seen more than two trucks at a time. I'm guessing he'll have ten to twelve men with lots of guns.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan checks the rifle and hands it to her. His fingertips are purple, his face has lost oxygen. They're so close, but the signs are obvious now. Jagan is dying.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We'll have to even the odds.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CuT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Forest treeline</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see our hero's truck abandoned just off of the road as they head into the woods, a quick pace, looking for the battle ahead, or to be left alone... whichever comes first.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">One Force trucks come pulling up to the abandoned vehicle. They hop out, quiet, tactical. Begin spreading into the tree line. Gunny hangs back a bit. Takes in a deep breath through his nose. Evil satisfaction.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men, including Gunny, dressed in all black, rifles up,are now quietly moving through the forest. The point man looks through the trees and signs "all clear" to the rest. One of the men, JUNO, (30's Hispanic) spots a broken branch and yells to the others.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Juno</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I got something!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Juno goes barreling toward the hanging limb, eager to be the one to win the bragging rights. He peeps back to see if Gunny is watching. Gunny looks on but doesn't respond.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Juno has to jump over a fallen log on his way when- YANK! Juno's head snaps back and his body does a half-flip landing face-up. The other men catch up and see him now on his back, gasping for air with blood pouring from a deep slit in his neck.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The others catch up and are a little dumbfounded looking at each other. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson catches up and jumps into action, trying to stop the bleeding.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Johnson</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">C'mon, Juno. Stay with me. Kelly get to the truck and get the first aid kit, we gotta get this wound closed up--</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">POW! Blood splatters all over Johnson as he looks down and sees a single bullet hole in the skull of Juno. The men look at Gunny, who's pistol is still smoking from the shot.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">He wasn't gonna make it anyway. Keep moving.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Off Johnson looking at Juno's dead face, we-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Deep IN THE FOREST</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Two soldiers moving stealthily in the tree line, everything has them scared. Every animal, every sound. One stops the other from walking into a neck high wire obviously placed by Jagan. He points it out to the others. Gunny catches up and laughs about it. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">He must be running out of ideas. But you won't be getting us with the same trick twice.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny strums the wire with his gloved hand like a guitar string.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Camera angle follows the wire from his finger down to the tree where it is connected, to find a tiny bell hanging from it that is now ringing from the vibration.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Realization hits Gunny as POW! One of the men drop from a headshot. Gunny tucks behind a tree as two shots take out another man from what seems to be another location. The men struggle to find their bearings. POW! A third man drops and the rest scramble to find cover. Running away, one of the men trip over the low wire that Jagan set earlier. He howls in pain.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GuNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Shut up!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">A frustrated Gunny maneuvers over to the downed man and flips him over to find the knives that Jagan buried, sticking out of the man's torso. This even takes Gunny aback. The man tries to pull out one of the knives himself, unsuccessfully. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I got it, I got it.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny manages to pry out the first knife from the ribs as his soldier riles in pain. Gunny looks disappointed, but wastes no time  sticking the knife right back into the man's heart and yanking it to widen the hole. He dies in shock, but quickly.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Shit...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny stands, looking deep into the green of the forest as if he's talking to a spirit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
<Text Style="">(yelling)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Got a little fight left in you, huh Jagan? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny quips to himself as if he's relishing this moment. CRACK! Another mercenary drops. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fuck! You gonna wait till he runs out, or shoot back? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">CRACK! This next shot just misses Gunny's head and hits a tree. He ducks and laughs a little.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The rest of One Force start shooting in the direction that the shots came from. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Fan out. We're right where he wants us here.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men tactically spread out and begin to move forward, one cautious step at a time.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We hear the distinct sound of a knife being removed from it's sheath when SHANK! The handle of a blade is all we see as another soldier drops and the surrounding men begin letting off shots in the origin of the throw. When the gunfire subsides, one man is yelling.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Kelly</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I got him! I fucking got him!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Kelly starts toward his prize, but Gunny stops him, eyeing his remaining forces. Four men left. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Johnson, take the point. Any man that gets shot or stabbed is dead. There is no place for the crippled in my unit.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny makes eye contact with Johnson who immediately takes off.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson and the squad creep through the woods gingerly. We see the world through their eyes. Tunnel vision as they navigate.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Johnson spots blood on one of the trees. JAGAN WAS HIT. Johnson turns to the next man who is fifteen yards back and gives the signal to stay put. The silent signal is relayed back amongst the group.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The lone point man creeps ahead with his rifle at the ready position and we see from his POV a portion of Jagan's leg from behind a tree and hear heavy breathing. Johnson circles around to reveal an injured Jagan, shot in the thigh being held by Ma'at. Off of everyone making shocked eye contact we-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">DEEP IN THE FOREST - MOMENTS LATER</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny is waiting with the men to hear word when, from the distance we hear-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JoHNSON (O.S.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Gunny!</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny perks up.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Finally.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The three remaining men with Gunny make their way to the origin of the sound.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">The remaining men casually stroll around to see Jagan holding Johnson hostage with a handgun to his head. Gunny eyes the scene. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Got dammit, you are putting me through a lotta trouble! </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Turn around. Stop following us, Gunny... and no one else will have to die.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Oh hell Jagan... you know somebody's always gotta die.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">POW! Gunny shoots Johnson a couple of times in the body. Jagan and his hostage drop to the ground.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Gunny walks right up to the sight. Pulls Johnson's body off of Jagan, who is bleeding from two spots on his torso. One is near his heart. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Told ya.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny kicks Jagan in his ribs a few times.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Had to take a man hostage, Jagan? Apparently, you didn't believe you could take me in a shootout.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Jagan spits blood as he talks and tries to get to his feet.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Actually, I was just I outta ammo... But if you'd like to give me a fresh magazine-</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan readies himself into a fighter's stance as if to challenge Gunny.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Damn, I wish we could have done this under better circumstances. Now look at you...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan stammers a bit, spits blood. His left shoulder has a gunshot wound and that hand won't raise.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Tired, shot, beaten... and The Blue is all over you... hell, your heart is probably already pumping cold blood through your body. If I didn't kill you, you'd be dead soon anyway.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny looks around the forest to see his surroundings.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But what the hell...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Gunny kicks Jagan square in the chest so hard that Jagan is lifted off of the ground. Jagan lands and can barely lift himself back up. Gunny kicks away the arm Jagan is using to support himself and turns him over with a few more kicks. Gunny wipes some sweat from his brow and turns to his men.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Go get her, and you better have your fun now... cuz when I get her... it ain't gone be nothin' left. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">A barely conscious Jagan tries to move and Gunny steps on his gunshot wound. Jagan yells in agony.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Where you going? No, no, no. I need you to stay alive long enough to hear her beg me to stop.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at is breathing heavily, hiding behind a tree. She looks another direction and sees one of the soldiers in front of her. Now all three men are in front of her, her back against the tree.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan can barely breathe. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">I know you, Jagan. You wanna kill them for what you feel are the vicious, animalistic things they're about to do to her. But it ain't their fault. This wicked earth has stolen from us all. And you've been hoarding that which was meant for us to share.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men are taking off their battle gear, guns, belts, etc.. Ma'at is cornered, not making eye contact.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny digging into Jagan's wound as he speaks. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You know how long I waited for what you been keeping from me?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Gunny punches Jagan in the face.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">GUNNY</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">And what made you think you were special? Do you believe she's yours? Did you think that she belongs to you? </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Jagan, eyes glossy, near death responds.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">No. I belong to her. I protect her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">The men are moving in to grab Ma'at. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO: JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Gunny</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Well, damn boy. You failed. The moment you made me hunt her down, you failed.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Aww shit, Gunny. You have no idea do you?</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Ma'at</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From beneath her locks Ma'at looks up for the first time at the men. Slow motion shows her "Protect Her" blades whip out from her hands.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">You waited too long.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Close up of Ma'at shows her teeth gritted as she leaps into attack mode. Her blades slashing into the legs, bodies and necks of her attackers. Violent, unforgiving.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut to: Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see Gunny's horrified look and hear the screams of his men being ripped to shreds as Jagan talks. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This world that you can barely breathe in has made her strong...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Cut to Ma'at on top of the last body, pulling her blade from the back of his head. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Jagan</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">This air, this sun, this world, is hers. You are not the hunter anymore. You... are the prey. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at moves like a charging panther. Gunny hearing the noises getting closer, runs for his life through the unfamiliar forest but short on breath and heart, Ma'at easily overtakes him and launches herself into the air, as Gunny turns around just in time to see his death blocking out the sun on her way down. She lands blades first into him. From Jagan's POV we see the action out of focus as Ma'at makes Gunny pay for his actions.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at finishes and finds Jagan. Bleeding out. She picks him up. Our shot changes to the inside of a One Force SUV. Jagan is sleeping on the passenger side, Ma'at is driving. Looking at him with concern, Avee is looking on, standing on her hind legs in between the seats.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Treeline - giant redwood forest</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We see the SUV recklessly parked with the passenger door still open. Jagan narrates.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">We made it to the forest of her childhood...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">(camera pans down from the treetops to reveal a gigantic tree with a majestic base)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">JAGAN (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">She worked quickly to let me drink from its sap. To taste its essence and I humbly asked this earth to breathe its air, taste its water, and to see the sunlight dance on the face of the one I loved most...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Pull away shot reveals Jagan and Ma'at in an embrace. Jagan's body is limp.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Seasons change. We see Ma'at on her knees. She's talking as the shot pulls out to reveal her surroundings. She feels fully indigenous now. Feathers in hair, sun kissed skin, native clothing. Also, very visibly pregnant.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Maybe we were just too late. Or this earth did not trust the species of man enough to grant our request.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We can now see that she is at a plot of dirt, in the middle of grass, surrounded by trees. There is a large, natural stone a few feet away. Marking the spot. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">But we were given a precious gift.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">We flash forward in time and see Mother and daughter, Ma'at and Moonlight (Looks to be around 6 or 7 years old wild hair, her mother's child) both fully indigenous. Obviously in clothes made by Ma'at as they feed a small horse passing by.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">My daughter has never seen another person, and the environment has changed so over the past two years that the old humans couldn't have survived.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. Jagan's grave site - AFTERNOON</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">The shot looks up at Ma'at and has a small out of focus plant in the frame (dirty), a baby tree in the middle of the plot. </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">Ma'at pours her heart out to Jagan.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">She'll be two years old in the coming days, but she has the growth of a much older child. And she's so curious. She's so curious, Jagan. She knows so much about you. She's got your heart. You were supposed to be here... You said you'd come back to me... </Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">FADE TO:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">Flashback - Jagan in the truck</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">We see a flashback from earlier of Jagan looking at her, when he says "Always".</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Flash to:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">EXT. JAGAN'S GRAVE SITE - CONTINUOUS</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Ma'at grips the dirt. We see the leaves of this tiny tree barely blowing in the breeze, not giving her the response she's pleading for.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">(SNAP) The sound of a twig breaking catches her attention. Ma'at looks around for Moonlight who we see up in a tree, also looking for the source of the noise. Another footstep and Ma'at can see something. With the ease of a squirrel, Moonlight drops from the tree right beside her mother to get a better look.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">Until we finally see. A small boy, even smaller than Moonlight. With dark skin and Asian features. Looking at them as if he has no idea what they are.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text></Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">In a blink, the indigenous boy is gone. By his speed we know that he is a child of this new world. Moonlight looks at Ma'at for approval. A slight nod of Ma'at's head and Moonlight is off to the races. All we really see is the movement of the bushes as she darts off. Ma'at breathes. Satisfied, as she looks on we hear the sounds of children playing.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">MA'AT (V.O.)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
<Text Style="">Moonlight will not have to grow up alone. There are others, very few but others still. This bitter earth has purged herself of everything that was making her ill. Everyday her water flows clearer, her air is cleaner, her life is stronger. This time we will do better. This time we will protect her.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Action">
<Text Style="">From a close up of Ma'at's face we:</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">CUT TO BLACK.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Credits roll</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Scene Heading">
<SceneProperties Title=""><Summary>
	<Paragraph Alignment="Left" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="0.00" RightIndent="1.39" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
		<Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style=""></Text>
	</Paragraph>
</Summary></SceneProperties><Text Style="AllCaps">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="General">
<Text Style="">*</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Additional ending</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Character">
<Text Style="AllCaps">As Ma'at is still taking in the sights and reflecting, her hair moves over her ear as if it's being guided by a hand. She turns around and the wide angle shows she is all alone. She ponders and looks at Jagan's grave site. A tree in the dirt. It seems somehow slightly bigger than a few minutes before. She stares, confused. Turns away. Turns back to see...</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Shot">
<Text Style="AllCaps">(omitted)</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Cut TO BLACK.</Text>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph Type="Transition">
<Text Style="AllCaps">Additional credits</Text>
</Paragraph>
